US government spending grew at slower rate, +0.7% in Q4, down from +1.8% in Q3. Added +0.1 ppt to GDP, down from +0.3 ppts in Q3.
Widening US trade deficit shaved -0.5 ppts from GDP in Q4, on top of -0.3 ppts in Q3.
US exports fell -2.5% in Q4, as opposed to rising +0.7% in Q3. Imports rose +1.1% in Q4, down from +2.3%.
Decline in inventories shaved -0.5 ppts from US GDP in Q4, on top of -0.7 ppts in Q3.
US housing investment remained strong, grew +8.1% in Q4 (vs +8.2% in Q3). Added +0.3 ppts to GDP, as in Q3.
US business investment fell -1.8% in Q4, vs growing +2.6% in Q3. Subtracted -0.2 ppts from GDP, vs adding +0.3 ppts in Q3.
US consumption growth slowed from +3.0% in Q3 to +2.2% in Q4. Added +1.5 ppts to GDP, down from +2.0 ppts in Q3.
